Chelsea could be handed $5million (£3.68m) if the Blues are able to win this season’s FIFA Club World Cup trophy. The west London club, who were crowned UEFA Champions League winners last season, will be bidding to win their first-ever Club World Cup in their second appearance in the competition. 10 years ago, Rafael Benitez led his Chelsea side out against Corinthians in the final of the CWC, but the Brazilian team came out 1-0 winners on the day. Chelsea’s Latest Wage Bill Revealed Everton To Launch Summer Move For Chelsea Starlet A decade on, Thomas Tuchel will be hoping to make history yet again as Blues boss, although the German’s presence in camp is still unknown as he is isolating with Covid-19 at the time of writing. There is a chance Tuchel will join up with his squad later in the week should they progress past Saudi Arabian side Al-Hilal in the semi-final on Wednesday afternoon. The German coach will be doing everything in his power to ensure the west Londoners are crowned the best football club in the world – and if they do achieve that, then they could pocket around £3.68m from the prize fund, as per Sporting News. The report claims that the official prize money has not been confirmed by FIFA yet, but in other seasons, the pot has totalled at $16.5m (£12.1m) and that is expected to be shared between the seven clubs.